reviewText:
Greetings;

Well, I gave this title a five star review mostly because it had fairly decent animation, nothing really...Special, I suppose compared to other similar titles, but it was certainly decent enough to satisfy. My only real problem with the show was that, as another reviewer said, it was short. Specificially, too short. More to the point, the product description has it as being 60 minutes long when it was really only 30, closer to just being 25 minutes with the dual sets of credits that run at the end. I just really wish it had been longer, I mean, the main character only just got her powers, the other soldiers had to show up because they were all looking for her, which I can therefore understand why they would all be in the first episode instead of say, having them be revealed in future episodes, but still. Would have been much better if they had only thought to give it another episode, hell, why not two? a 90 minute dvd would have been fine with me too. Spaceship Agga Ruter, depending on which dvd of it you find-the complete series dvd has all 4 episodes on it-at two hours in length. All things considered though, I do suppose I lucked out and found this title fairly well priced, so I am still happy with it. So, you might consider looking into it.

Thank you...
